# Agent Lifecycle

## Single-Use Agents

Agents created for one-off, unformulated tasks (not part of a recurring workflow):

1. **Tag as single-use** — add `# single-use` in the module docstring so they are identifiable
2. **Cleanup prompt** — 3 days after creation, on the first interaction with the AI coding agent, ask the user:

> "The agent `<name>` was created 3 days ago for a one-off task. Would you like to remove it from the project?"

3. **If yes** — delete the agent file, remove any config entries, and update `README.md`
4. **If no** — remove the single-use tag; the agent becomes a permanent part of the project
